gomodel:SYNGO_459  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Localization of Munc13 isoforms at the calyx of Held synapse.\n25/4/2017 Pim\n- Fig.1 shows localization of native protein with subtype-specific antibodies. Strong colocalization with the presynaptic marker VGlut1 together with a lack of staining of the postsynaptic MNTB cell body strongly support a presynaptic localization.\n- Fig.2/3 shows localization of genetically encoded EGFP attached to native mouse Munc13 paralogs. Strong colocalization with the presynaptic markers VGlut1 and Bassoon together with a lack of staining of the postsynaptic MNTB cell body strongly support a presynaptic localization.. Experimental description: Generation of Munc13-2 KO and Munc13-3 KO and Munc13-2-3 double KO (DKO) mice have been described previously (Augustin et al., 2001; Varoqueaux et al., 2002). Munc13-XFP mice have been described previously (Kalla et al., 2006; Cooper et al., 2012)\n\n25/4/2017 Pim\n- Fig.2 and Fig.3 show localization of genetically encoded EGFP attached to native mouse Munc13 paralogs\n- Annotation to mouse protein is correct." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-27" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_459" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

